main event: A bright light was observed for 5 minutes near New Orleans, Louisiana on 7 April 1965.
interesting points: The observation was classified as Air-Visual., The light was reported to have moved in a NE direction., No definitive conclusion was reached regarding the object observed., The possible source was identified as an airborne aircraft-type device., The witness was Capt. Samuel V. Marshall from the Louisiana Air National Guard.
witness description: Capt. Samuel V. Marshall, Louisiana Air National Guard
